# Read Agent Entry Guide

Before making any code changes, you must read the repository root `agent.md`.

`agent.md` is the entry point for AI-assisted development in this project. It explains how to follow the project-wide development documents under `docs/`.

## Required behavior

When starting a task:

1. Read `agent.md` from the repository root.
2. Follow the document-reading workflow defined in `agent.md`.
3. Read the required project documents before editing code.
4. Do not skip architecture, glossary, API contract, data model, or coding-style documents when the task scope requires them.
5. If `agent.md` does not exist, stop and report that the project entry guide is missing.

## Important

The project rules are not defined in this Cursor rule.

This Cursor rule only requires you to start from `agent.md`.

The actual source of truth for development rules, architecture rules, domain glossary, API contracts, and data models is defined by the project documentation referenced from `agent.md`.